    Is your company website sick? Is it out-of-control, unorganized, hopelessly out-of-date? Does it just not look as clean and professional as your company and image deserve? Protect your company's image, clean up your information and improve your on-line presence with our site rescue services.<br>
    
    <br>
    <strong>Why Redesign?</strong><br>
    Our culture is changing rapidly as access to and use of the Internet become more pervasive. For increasing numbers of people around the world, instant access to information and choices has become not only a reality, but a given. Website addresses pervade the media, and it is now nearly a self-understood fact that a serious business has a presence on the web. Two years ago, the web was cutting-edge. Now, any large business without a website is almost a curiosity.<br>
    <br>
    Easy web creation tools and templates help many businesses get started. But in an increasing number of fields, it is no longer enough simply to have a website. To be taken seriously, the site must be good. It must provide users with a reason to come, to stay and to return. It has to fit the company image- to compliment existing <a href="brands.asp" target="main" class="linknorm">brand</a>, marketing and promotional efforts. It has to look professional and offer something- information, contacts, product or service news, support, a store front- something to impress an audience that enters and leaves with their impressions in minutes.
    </font>
