    <strong>Critical Impressions</strong><br>
    Users don't want to search too hard to find your site, and when they get there, their first impression must be good, or they will never return. If they come and your site is professional and easy to use, you may win their business. But if they come and see an outdated, amateur site- particularly if it doesn't match the caliber of your other promotional efforts- in mere seconds, your site may destroy the <a href="brands.asp" target="main" class="linknorm">professional impression</a> you have worked so hard to create.<br>
    <br>
    <strong>Rescue &amp; Enhancements</strong><br>
    Subterminal.com specializes in professional website re-design and construction. Let us help take the worry out of your electronic business front and give you a high-end site design worthy of your good business name. Advertising and marketing are critical to business success, and most successful businesses spend a good deal of time and effort creating a public impression. Many go to great lengths and spend a lot of money on printed promotional materials, TV ads and radio. But when it comes to the internet, too often a company's first (or second, or third) website does not get the same attention to professionalism and detail as other marketing efforts.<br>
